&nbsp;"I was sorry to see forcedness, wrong interpretations, sometimes even attacks on the Pontiff in this condition. I think this is the moment of prayer, of waiting or the time to express 'good waves', as the Pope says when he addresses those who are not believer." Thus the Jesuit Antonio Spadaro, among the closest collaborators of Pope Francis, in an interview with Repubblica. Regarding the possibility of resignation, Father Spadaro recalls that "in one of his trips he clearly said that the Papacy is alive. The idea of renouncing the Petrine ministry, already mentioned in the past, appears as a weighted option if the energies were irreversible."
