&nbsp;
Meanwhile, prayers for the health of Bergoglio have multiplied today. First, Monsignor Fisichella, who invited a "intensive" prayer for the Lord to assist Francis "at the time of trial and illness". The "his" diocese was also gathered in prayer. Cardinal Baldo Reina celebrated Mass in the Basilica of St. John in Lateran "with a special intercession for the health of Pope Francis" and the President of the Council, Cardinal Matteo Zuppi presided over the Rosary to ask God to support the Pope "at this time of suffering, so that he may find relief and be restored as soon as possible". &nbsp;
